FBIS4-57369 "drlat096_a_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-096 Daily Report 17 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Castro Congratulates Ciego de Avila Sugar Workers Castro Congratulates Ciego de Avila Sugar Workers FL1705135694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 GMT 17 May 94 FL1705135694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] Ciego de Avila farmers who have just received a message of praise from Commander in Chief Fidel Castro for the efforts being made in the current harvest have expressed their commitment to meet the sugar production plan despite current difficulties. During a visit by the commander in chief's Coordination and Support Staff, headed by Elida Valle, the fulfillment of the plan in several complexes, as well as the high spirit of production of the workers, was noted. Measures being implemented to stabilize the grinding were also noted, and it was reported that equipment from other provinces will arrive shortly to bolster the harvest effort in Ciego de Avila Province.
